# Network Troubleshooting Lab Diagram

## Basic Network Layout

```text
User Workstation
      │
      │ Ethernet / Wi-Fi
      │
Default Gateway / Router
      │
      │
Internet Service Provider
      │
      │
External Websites / Cloud Services
```

## Lab Testing Flow

```text
Local Computer
      ↓
TCP/IP Stack
      ↓
Network Adapter
      ↓
IP Address / DHCP
      ↓
Default Gateway
      ↓
DNS Server
      ↓
Internet Destination
```

## Troubleshooting Path

```text
Step 1: Check IP configuration
Step 2: Test loopback address
Step 3: Test local IP address
Step 4: Test default gateway
Step 5: Test external IP address
Step 6: Test DNS resolution
Step 7: Trace route to destination
Step 8: Document findings
```

## Example Lab Network Information

| Item | Example |
|---|---|
| Workstation IP | 192.168.1.25 |
| Subnet Mask | 255.255.255.0 |
| Default Gateway | 192.168.1.1 |
| DNS Server | 192.168.1.1 or 8.8.8.8 |
| DHCP Range | 192.168.1.100 - 192.168.1.200 |
| Network Type | Private lab network |

## Purpose

This diagram shows the basic path network traffic takes from a user workstation to an external internet destination. It also helps identify where a network issue may be occurring.
